<p>As usual Profesor Bardi is right on. His comment about recycling being viewed as &#8216;subversive&#8217;. We hear about ,reduce, reuse and recycle a lot now. The problem is, were dont really mean it. O we like talking about it, and acting like we are actually are re-using stuff, but no. Only a tiny fraction of the stuff we toss out truely gets recycled in any meaningful way, most is simply compacted into large globs of whatever it is for easier disposal.Most of us are only vaguely aware of where our regular trash goes, and when it comes to all the stuff we think were recycling, we know even less. The entire economy we have prevents recyling all by itself, its built right into it. Of course, the best way to prevent trash is not to make it in the first place, or alternately, build things to last. Neither of which are features of &#8216;modern&#8217; economies.</p>
