<div style="float:left;margin:3px 20px 10px 0px;"><img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/115e45607915788505f5b4493daf72ba?s=96&amp;d=&amp;r=X' class='avatar avatar-96 photo' height='96' width='96'/></div>
<p>This is the way indeed and it is almost certain that it is not the one we will choose voluntarily. </p>
<p>Our consumer society is based on absurd principles: Unlimited growth, unlimited availability of energy, ignorance of cycles, expectation of unrealistic returns on capital and investment, etc&#8230; </p>
<p>This is unlikely to change without a crisis of such magnitude that our social structures won&#8217;t survive it.</p>
<p>Dr Ugo Bardi is simply showing that we can all understand what should be done individually but not as a society. </p>
<p>This I believe is the crux of the problem and I am afraid there is no solution.</p>
</div>
