<div class="commentleft">
<li class="alt" id="comment-24668">
<p><b>Kenz300 on Tue, 5th Jun 2012 12:20 pm&nbsp;</b></p>
<div style="float:left;margin:3px 20px 10px 0px;"><img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/b185ed68760007abf9023767e2b593b7?s=96&amp;d=&amp;r=X' class='avatar avatar-96 photo' height='96' width='96'/></div>
<p>Waste Management is the worlds largest waste handling company. They are making huge investments into developing systems that use the trash or waste as a resource. They estimate that the value of the waste and the biofuels, energy and raw materials can be developed into an income stream that matches or exceeds what the company currently brings in. That would double the size of the company by using the waste as a resource.</p>
</div>
